appTitle: Google Duo - High Quality Video Calls
reviewTitle: I originally left a one-star review because I thought this was a poor replacement for Hangouts. I've since learned two things. 1) Hangouts for personal use is going to be deprecated. 2) Google made a lot of improvements to Duo. It's a much better app now.  It would be a better app if it would allow text messages as well. It would be Google's answer to iMessage, which is one of the few things like like about iOS. In fact, having Duo do text messages would make it a superior product to iMessage and Facetime, since neither of those are available on Android platforms.  For now, I'll have to stick with my carrier's SMS/MMS and Google Voice.
